    <!-- article titles and content -->
    <string name="article_1_title">Top 5 Fishing Spots in the UK</string>
    <string name="article_1_body">From the crystal-clear rivers of Scotland to the tranquil lakes of the Lake District, the UK offers world-class fishing locations. Whether you prefer fly fishing for trout or coarse fishing for carp, these spots guarantee an unforgettable experience.</string>
    <string name="article_2_title">Essential Camping Gear for Beginners</string>
    <string name="article_2_body">Heading outdoors for the first time? Start with a quality 3-season tent, a sleeping bag rated for your climate, a portable stove, and a reliable headlamp. Invest in durable, lightweight gear that will last many seasons.</string>
    <string name="article_3_title">How to Choose the Right Fishing Rod</string>
    <string name="article_3_body">The right rod depends on the type of fishing you plan to do. Spinning rods are versatile and great for beginners. Consider the rod\'s length, power, and action to find your perfect match for your target species.</string>
    <string name="article_4_title">Best Mountain Biking Trails in the UK</string>
    <string name="article_4_body">The UK is home to some of Europe\'s best mountain biking trails. Glentress in Scotland offers world-class routes. Afan Forest in Wales provides challenging descents through pine forests perfect for all skill levels.</string>
    <string name="article_5_title">Camping Safety Tips for Outdoor Enthusiasts</string>
    <string name="article_5_body">Always tell someone your plans before heading out. Carry a first aid kit, map and compass, and enough food and water. Learn basic weather reading skills and know when to turn back. Stay safe and enjoy the outdoors.</string>

